Work Experience

Here is the timeline

Sr. Software Enginner at Evolent Health, Arlington, VA Feb 2016 - present

  • Extensively works on various modules of sophisticated value based health care platform in all phases of SDLC, modules includes Utilization Management, Care Management, Practice, Engage.
  • Contributed significantly in the design and development of .Net Framework, .Net Core infrastructure for our platform which is the base for all our services code base.
  • Unit test, Integration tests, Code reviews, CI/CD are also integral part of my work.
  • Worked on various new, existing projects as well as major migration project in which we switched our application from single tenant to multi tenant.
  • Key role in projects that are built on web, mobile, windows platforms as a full stack developer.
  • Worked on Microservices, Distributed applications and their architecture.
  • Responsible for monitoring applications and their fixes for performance improvements when needed.
  • Technologies, Tools, Environments: C#, JavaScript, Sql, NoSql, .Net Framework, .Net Core, React, React native, Angular js, node js, Visual Studio, VS Code, SSMS, Azure Devops, Github, ELK, Redis, Rabbitmq, App Insights, Postman, REST services, Mac Os, Windows, Linux.

Application Developer at Citizens Financial Group, Cleveland, OH Jan 2015 - Feb 2016

  • Extensively worked on the development and enhancement of Empower application, a Loan Originating system.
  • Developed SSIS projects in order to make tasks simpler for transfer of data between database servers.
  • Extended support for testing and resolving the tickets in various projects.
  • Worked on reporting applications using crystal reports.
  • Received Citizens credo award for my work.
  • Technologies, Tools, Environments: C#, Win Forms, Web Services, REST services, Visual Studio, Microsoft SQL Server, SSIS, Crystal Reports, WCF, Windows.

Software Development Intern at Hyland Software, Westlake, OH May 2014 - Aug 2014

  • Developed a troubleshooting and analysis tool aimed at EIS/BizTalk customers.
  • This tool is used to analyze common issues of EIS databases and Biz Talk server.
  • This tool Reduces the amount of time Tech Support is engaged to track down an EIS issue, which reduces the company costs, as well as resolving common issues more quickly which will make the customer happier.
  • Technologies, Tools, Environments: C#, WPF, Web Services, Visual Studio, Microsoft SQL Server, Biz Talk Server, Onbase.

Web Developer at Institutional Research, The University of Akron, Akron, OH Jan 2013 - Dec 2014

  • Involved in the development and maintenance of web applications that portray the statistical data by Institutional Research department.
  • Created and updated the supporting database tables, stored procedures for asp.net web applications.
  • Involved in design, development and maintenance of website for Institutional Research.
  • Technologies, Tools, Environments: C#, .Net Framework, Oracle, MS Access, Visual Studio, SQL Developer, Dot Cms
